\li1 Beriah’s sons Heber and Malkiel;
\li1 (Those were the children and grandchildren of Jacob and Zilpah, the slave girl whom Laban gave to his daughter Leah: There were 16 of them, altogether.)
\li1 Joseph and Benjamin, the sons of Jacob’s wife Rachel;
\li1 (Ephraim and Manasseh were Joseph’s two sons. \add They did not go down to Egypt\add* because they were already in Egypt. They were sons of Asenath, the daughter of On, who was the priest in the temple in On \add city\add*.)
\li1 Benjamin and his sons Bela, Beker, Ashbel, Gera, Naaman, Ehi, Rosh, Muppim, Huppim, and Ard;
\li1 (Those were the sons and grandsons of Rachel and Jacob: There were 14 people altogether.)
\li1 Dan and his son Hushim;
\li1 Naphtali and his sons Jahziel, Guni, Jezer, and Shillem.
